        <div class="verdict">✓ Updated April 2026</div>

        <p>General contractor is a broad label. A GC building custom homes in suburban Nashville has entirely different software needs than a GC building a $40M medical office building. Project type, company size, and what you're trying to solve all determine which software is right for your business.</p>

        <p>This guide cuts through the options by matching GC type to the right platform.</p>

        <h2>Residential GCs: Buildertrend is the standard</h2>
        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Custom homebuilders, residential remodeling GCs, design-build firms serving residential clients</p>
        <p><strong>Price:</strong> $499–$1,099/mo</p>

        <p>Buildertrend dominates residential GC software because it was built specifically for this market. The platform covers the complete residential project lifecycle: lead management, estimating, scheduling, client portal, selections, change orders, subcontractor management, financial tracking, and QuickBooks integration.</p>

        <p>The key features that matter for residential GCs:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Client portal</strong> — Homeowners log in to see schedule, progress photos, approve change orders, and make payments. This eliminates the constant "how's my house going" phone calls and creates a paper trail for every client decision</li>
          <li><strong>Selections management</strong> — Track every owner selection from cabinets to tile to light fixtures with allowance tracking and approval records. When a client claims they never chose that countertop, you have documentation</li>
          <li><strong>Subcontractor bid requests</strong> — Send scoped bid requests to your sub list, track responses, and convert accepted bids to purchase orders</li>
          <li><strong>Gantt scheduling with dependencies</strong> — When framing gets pushed, the schedule cascades automatically. Subs get notified when their window is approaching</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="cta-box">
          <p><strong>Buildertrend</strong> — The go-to platform for residential GCs. Request a demo to see how it fits your specific business.</p>
          <a href="https://www.buildertrend.com" rel="nofollow sponsored" target="_blank" class="btn">Visit Buildertrend →</a>
