        <h2>Smaller residential GCs: JobTread or Houzz Pro</h2>
        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> GCs under $1.5M annual revenue who can't justify Buildertrend's price</p>

        <p><strong>JobTread ($99–$499/mo)</strong> — Covers estimating, job costing, scheduling, and client communication at a fraction of Buildertrend's cost. The job costing is particularly strong — real-time budget vs. actual that tells you whether you're making money before the job closes.</p>

        <p><strong>Houzz Pro ($65–$399/mo)</strong> — Better for design-forward remodeling GCs who want lead generation from the Houzz marketplace and client proposals that reflect their design brand.</p>

        <h2>Commercial GCs: Procore is the standard</h2>
        <p><strong>Best for:</strong> GCs doing commercial, institutional, multi-family, or public works projects</p>
        <p><strong>Price:</strong> Custom</p>

        <p>For commercial GCs, Procore is the dominant choice. The RFI and submittal workflows, drawing management, and subcontractor financial management are the most mature in the industry for commercial construction. Owners and architects on your commercial projects are likely already using Procore or familiar with it.</p>

        <p>The key differentiators for commercial GCs:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Formal RFI and submittal tracking with timestamped audit trails</li>
          <li>Drawing version control accessible by the full project team</li>
          <li>Subcontract financial management with pay applications (G702/G703)</li>
          <li>500+ integrations with scheduling, ERP, and accounting systems</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Mid-size commercial GCs: Consider Autodesk Build</h2>
        <p>If your company uses Revit or other Autodesk design tools, Autodesk Build is worth evaluating alongside Procore. The native BIM integration is a real advantage for GCs on complex, BIM-heavy commercial projects.</p>

        <h2>For field coordination on any size project: Fieldwire</h2>
        <p>Many GCs — both residential and commercial — use Fieldwire alongside their primary PM platform specifically for field coordination. Supers and subs access current drawings, complete punch lists, and log daily reports without needing access to the full PM system. The free tier (3 active projects) makes it easy to trial.</p>

